Package com.example.donotredeem

Enum Class MoodType

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<MoodType>
com.example.donotredeem.MoodType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<MoodType>, Constable
public enum MoodType extends Enum<MoodType>
Enum representing different mood types along with their associated drawable image resource IDs. Each mood type is defined with a descriptive name and a corresponding drawable resource.

    • getImageIdByMood

      public static int getImageIdByMood(String mood)
      Returns the drawable image resource ID associated with the specified mood name. The search is case-insensitive and iterates over all available mood types. If no matching mood is found, -1 is returned.
      Parameters:
      mood - the name of the mood (e.g., "Happy", "Sad", etc.)
      Returns:
      the drawable image resource ID if a match is found; -1 otherwise
